    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "Add Credentials - Google OAuth2\n\n1. Open Google Cloud Console\nGo to the Google Cloud Console.\nCreate a new project (or use an existing one).\n2. Enable the YouTube API\nEnable YouTube Data API v3 for your project.\n3. Configure the OAuth consent screen\nGo to APIs & Services → OAuth consent screen.\nChoose External (unless you're using a Google Workspace organization).\nFill in the required app information.\nAdd your Google account as a Test User if the app is still in testing.\n4. Create OAuth credentials\nGo to APIs & Services → Credentials.\nClick Create Credentials → OAuth Client ID.\nChoose Web application.\nAdd the redirect URI that n8n provides (you can see it in the OAuth credential setup screen in n8n).\nClick Create.\n\nGoogle will show you:\n\nClient ID\nClient Secret\n\nCopy both into the n8n OAuth2 credential.",
